      "content": "To write this raw material accurately without caricature, focus on the sheriff's *intent*—he's asserting absolute, unchallenged power. His language should feel performative, as if he is reciting accepted social rules rather than simply being irrational. You can achieve historical accuracy by researching primary source material like local newspaper accounts or court transcripts from that era to see how prejudice was legally and socially codified. Conveying the sheer weight of his authority through his delivery is just as important as the specific words he uses.",
